rived%20in%20Italy%20today%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20G7%20summit.%20This%20is%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20first%20foreign%20visit%20after%20taking%20charge%20for%20the%20third%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20is%20not%20a%20part%20of%20the%20G7%20group%20but%20has%20been%20invited%20to%20the%20summit.%20Its%20participation%20is%20significant%20as%20a%20'voice%20of%20the%20global%20south'%2C%20a%20term%20that%20Foreign%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20in%20the%20past.%20During%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20Indian%20soldiers%20played%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20campaign%20of%20the%20Allied%20forces%20to%20liberate%20Italy%20from%20Benito%20Mussolini's%20Fascist%20regime%20and%20Nazi%20Germany.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2050%2C000%20Indian%20soldiers%20fought%20in%20Italy%20during%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%20Six%20of%2020%20Victoria%20Crosses%2C%20Britain's%20highest%20gallantry%20award%2C%20given%20to%20soldiers%20in%20the%20Italian%20theatre%20of%20war%20were%20conferred%20on%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Heroics%20Of%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Allied%20invasion%20of%20Europe%20to%20liberate%20occupied%20countries%20from%20the%20Nazis%20and%20Fascist%20Italy%20began%20in%201943.%20The%20D-Day%20landings%20in%20Normandy%20in%201944%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20liberation%20of%20France.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20recruited%20young%20men%20in%20the%20Indian%20Army%20to%20fight%20in%20some%20of%20the%20most%20hostile%20battlefields.%20Young%20Kamal%20Ram%2C%20who%20would%20have%20been%2018%2C%20volunteered%2C%20and%20joined%20the%208th%20Punjab%20Regiment%20of%20the%20British%20Indian%20Army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20portrait%20of%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%20with%20the%20Imperial%20War%20Museum%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20portrait%20of%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%20with%20the%20Imperial%20War%20Museum%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F1i1rnn2_sepoy-kamal-ram_625x300_14_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20portrait%20of%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%20with%20the%20Imperial%20War%20Museum%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Image%3A%20IWM%20(Art.%20IWM%20ART%20LD%204516)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Orbat%20or%20Order%20of%20Battle%20was%204th%2C%208th%20and%2010th%20Infantry%20Divisions%20would%20be%20deployed%20to%20liberate%20Italy.%20Kamal%20Ram's%20regiment%20was%20part%20of%20the%208th%20Infantry%20Division.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Germans%20and%20Italians%20had%20built%20multiple%20fortifications%20called%20the%20Gustav%20Line%20which%20ran%20from%20the%20Tyrrhenian%20Sea%20in%20the%20west%20to%20the%20Adriatic%20Sea%20east.%20The%208th%20Infantry%20Division%20arrived%20in%20Italy%20via%20Syria%20in%20September%201943.%20Young%20Indians%2C%20who%20were%20just%2018%20and%20some%20were%2016%2C%20from%20Hindu%2C%20Sikh%2C%20and%20Muslim%20communities%20volunteered%20to%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Battle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2012%2C%201944%2C%20the%208th%20Punjab%20Regiment%20assaulted%20the%20Gustav%20Line.%20Just%20after%20crossing%20the%20River%20Gari%2C%20his%20company%20was%20surrounded%20by%20four%20German%20machine%20gun%20positions%20on%20the%20front%20and%20flanks.%20Securing%20the%20post%20was%20crucial%20to%20defend%20a%20bridgehead.%20The%20company%20commander%20asked%20for%20volunteers%20to%20secure%20the%20post%20by%20outflanking%20the%20enemy%20from%20the%20right%2C%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%2C%2019%2C%20said%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20crawled%20through%20the%20barbed%20wire%20and%20attacked%20the%20enemy%20position%20through%20a%20flank.%20He%20killed%20a%20German%20soldier%2C%20silencing%20the%20machine%20gun.%20When%20another%20German%20tried%20to%20seize%20his%20weapon%2C%20in%20close%20combat%2C%20Kamal%20Ram%20killed%20him%20with%20his%20bayonet%20attached%20to%20the%20rifle.%20A%20German%20officer%2C%20to%20Sepoy%20Ram's%20surprise%2C%20emerged%20from%20the%20trenches%20and%20shot%20him%20dead.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20moved%20to%20the%20second%20machine%20gun%20position%2C%20which%20was%20holding%20the%20company's%20advance.%20He%20lobbed%20grenades%20and%20silenced%20the%20enemy%20guns%20and%20the%20remaining%20enemy%20surrendered.%20He%20moved%20forward%20to%20assist%20a%20company%20Havildar%20who%20was%20attacking%20the%20third%20gun%20position%20and%20covered%20for%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20post.%20He%20single-handedly%20took%20control%20of%20two%20machine%20gun%20positions%20and%20helped%20take%20on%20the%20third.%20The%20display%20of%20courage%20was%20vital%20to%20secure%20the%20bridgehead%20and%20establish%20two%20bridges%20for%20the%20incoming%20forces%20to%20cross%20the%20river.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20when%20a%20platoon%20moved%20forward%2C%20Germans%20hiding%20in%20a%20house%2C%20fired%20on%20the%20incoming%20troops.%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram%20dashed%20toward%20the%20house%2C%20killed%20one%20German%20and%20captured%20two%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20service%2C%20King%20George%20VI%2C%20pinned%20a%20Victoria%20Cross%2C%20the%20highest%20gallantry%20award%2C%20to%20Sepoy%20Kamal%20Ram's%20chest%20on%20May%2027%2C%201944%2C%20in%20Italy.%20He%20was%20the%20second%20youngest%20Indian%20to%20be%20awarded%20the%20Victoria%20Cross.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Official%20Gazette%20notification%20archived%20by%20The%20National%20Archives%2C%20Kew%2C%20UK%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Official%20Gazette%20notification%20archived%20by%20The%20National%20Archives%2C%20Kew%2C%20UK%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fsepgn4t8_sepoy-kamal-ram_625x300_14_June_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFitAndFill%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C